//80. Remove Duplicates from Sorted Array II
//https://leetcode.com/problems/remove-duplicates-from-sorted-array-ii/



class Solution {
    public int removeDuplicates(int[] nums) {
        if(nums.length<=2)
        return nums.length;
        int k=2;
        for(int i=2;i<nums.length;i++){
            if(nums[k-2]!=nums[i]){
                nums[k++]=nums[i];
            }
        }
        return k;
    }
}


/*
nums = [1,1,1,2,2,3]
Step by step:

Start with k = 0.

First two numbers â†’ always keep.
â†’ [1, 1] âœ…

Now check the next 1:
Compare with nums[k-2].

nums[k-2] = 1 and current = 1 â†’ same! âŒ skip it.

Next number 2:
Compare with nums[k-2] = 1.

Different â†’ keep it â†’ [1, 1, 2].

Next 2:
Compare with nums[k-2] = 1.

Different â†’ keep it â†’ [1, 1, 2, 2].

Next 3:
Compare with nums[k-2] = 2.

Different â†’ keep it â†’ [1, 1, 2, 2, 3].

âœ… Done â†’ new length = 5, array = [1,1,2,2,3].

ðŸ’¡ Hint rule:
ðŸ‘‰ Always keep the first 2 elements.
ðŸ‘‰ For later elements, only keep if itâ€™s not equal to nums[k-2].

Do you want me to give you a formula-like rule you can directly apply in your loop?
*/
